net.dean.jraw.models

Enum ThingType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ThingType>
      • net.dean.jraw.models.ThingType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ThingType>

    public enum ThingType
extends java.lang.Enum<ThingType>
    An enumeration of types of objects in Reddit's API. Each type has a prefix of "t[0-6,8]". When this prefix, an underscore, and the ID of the Thing are combined in that order, you get that Thing's full name (Thing.getFullName()). For example, the subreddit /r/funny has a prefix of "t5", an ID of "2qh33", and a full name of "t5_2qh33"
